Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Retail Investments are delighted to present a rare opportunity to acquire an exclusive metro retail investment leased to EB Games, the largest gaming retailer in Australia with over 450 stores across the nation.

Located approximately 22km south of the Brisbane CBD and is positioned in a high profile, easily accessible location on the high street of Village Square – which has direct access to Grand Plaza Shopping Centre. Eastern
Road would unquestionably, be the best high street in Logan City and benefits from daily patronage, exposure to vehicles in either direction, complementing uses, not to mention an extremely favourable demographic.

Investors that are looking for certain income growth (4% fixed reviews) with security via a 2+ year WALE should strongly consider this opportunity. We detail a number of highlights below: 

Established, Proven Investment 
Well established tenancy with a proven high-income profile that is underpinned by the largest gaming retailer in Australia, operating over 470 EB Games stores, over 40 in New Zealand as well as over 80 Zing Pop Culture stores across Australia.

High, Certain Income Growth
Guaranteed income growth through an attractive rental review mechanism of 4% annual fixed increases.

Established Retailing Precinct 
Positioned in the heart of the Village Square precinct, the property also benefits from being part of a larger retail destination, which includes Grand Plaza Shopping Centre.

Investment Security Ideal for SMSF Investors 
Favorable lease structure with net income of $72,900 per annum to an established tenant, recently shutting their store within the Grand Plaza Shopping Center to direct all traffic to this flagship store.

Prime Exposure & Incredible Location 
Strategically positioned in a dominant location along Logan’s most popular high street, commanding a prominent frontage amongst complimenting retail tenants such as JB Hi-Fi, Good Life Health Clubs and other fast food tenancies supported by ample park to the front and rear of the tenancy.

Strong Retailing Expenditure Within Trade Area 
The Main Trade Area is forecasted for a major growth surge of 4.8% per annum as the surrounding residential population is growing well over the Queensland average.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: HIGH STREET LOGAN RETAIL INVESTMENT WITH NATIONAL TENANT

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
* Well established tenancy and income profile that is anchored by the largest gym group within Australia and 65% of the income underpinned by a multibillion private equity fund, providing absolute income security.

* A dominant, high profile freestanding retail investment, strategically positioned within Village Square Browns Plains, one of the largest home and lifestyle centres on Brisbane’s Southside.

* The investment boasts a secure income profile via a WALE of 5.49 years* by income with secured long-term leases to strong performing retailers Go Health, Rivers and Glamaco, who have all occupied the location since 2009.

* Guaranteed income growth through attractive rental review mechanisms of 3% and 4% annually.

* Significant retail expenditure in the main trade area which is forecast to see 4.8% pa growth. 

* Net Income: $1,013,641 per annum.

For Sale via Offers to purchase. Please contact the agents for more information.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: SECURE RETAIL INVESTMENT WITH ATTRACTIVE INCOME GROWTH

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
On behalf of the CBRE Queensland Retail Investments team, we are delighted to present this rare opportunity to purchase 48 Browns Plains Road, Browns Plains.

The property represents the opportunity to acquire a high-profile retail investment, strategically located in the heart of one of Brisbane southside's largest retail precincts.

- High-profile national tenants underpinning the income with Pet Barn (175+ stores) & Fernwood (69 stores), both on renewed 7 & 10 year lease terms respectively
- Established retail precinct & major retail hub opposite the $400m Grand Plaza & alongside high-profile retailers including Officeworks, BCF, Woolworths & McDonald's
- Dominant 66m* frontage along Browns Plains Road with exposure to over 10m cars annually
- High income growth with majority of the income profile growing a fixed 3% pa* 
- Convenient & easily accessible with direct access off Browns Plains Road & 250 at grade car parks available
- Secure income underpinned via an 8 year* WALE

THE PROPERTY IS FOR SALE VIA OFFERS TO PURCHASE.

A copy of the Information Memorandum and Due Diligence package is available upon request from the exclusively appointed CBRE agents.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: HIGH-PROFILE RETAIL INVESTMENT WITH STRONG NATIONAL TENANT LINEUP

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Opportunity
- $129,005 NET per annum
- Operator Cubby Care – experienced private QLD operator established for 15 years
- Leased till 2031
- Licenced 64 place LDC
- Lease commenced 27 February, 2016 
- 2 x 5 Year option remaining (notice period of five years and six months)
- Triple net lease – outgoings 100% recoverable including land tax on a single holding basis
- Rent reviews: CPI minimum 3% with next review 27/02/19
- Next Market review: year 11 - 2027
- Land size 2,566 sqm*
- 19 onsite car spaces

Building Description
- Semi-modern style (circa mid 1990’s construction), single level, purpose built childcare centre licensed for 64 long day care places. 
- The centre comprises five activity rooms, shared children’s amenities, staff room and reception and directors office. 
- Construction is primarily of brick external walls and sheet metal roofing. 

Location:
- 100 metres from Browns Plains State School
- 1 km from Browns Plains Grand Plaza shopping centre
- 2 km radius from Saint Bernardine's Catholic Primary School, Yugumbir State School and Regents Park State School 

For Sale by Expressions of Interest closing 4pm, Thursday 15th November, 2018

* approx.
